  "markdown_content": "\n## Executive Summary\n\nComplete development of Youniverse, a modular web application for creating personal multidimensional profiles across 7 chakra-inspired categories. The MVP includes full CRUD functionality, multiple export formats (JSON/Markdown/PDF), sharing capabilities with QR codes, responsive UI with dark/light modes, and local data persistence. The application was successfully built and prepared for deployment.\n\n\n## Context & Intent\n\nUser requested a comprehensive MVP for a personal profile mapping application inspired by the 7 chakras system, with requirements for editing, visualization, export, and sharing capabilities.\n\n\n## What Was Done\n\nBuilt complete React-based web application with 7 category system (Foundations, Relationships, Career, Health, Creativity, Vision, Mission), implemented accordion interface, real-time saving, progress tracking, export functionality (JSON/Markdown/PDF), QR code sharing, responsive design, and dark/light mode toggle.\n\n\n## Outputs Produced\n\n- [web_application] Youniverse MVP — Complete personal profile mapping application with 7 chakra categories\n- [user_interface] Responsive UI Components — Mobile-optimized interface with accordion panels and modern design\n- [export_system] Multi-format Export — JSON, Markdown, PDF export capabilities with sharing features\n\n## Key Decisions & Validations\n\n- Used localStorage for data persistence instead of backend database for MVP\n- Implemented accordion interface over mind map visualization for initial version\n- Built responsive-first design with mobile optimization\n- Chose React + Tailwind + shadcn/ui for rapid development\n\n## Lessons Learned\n\nWorked well:\n\n- Modular component architecture enabled rapid feature addition\n- Real-time progress tracking provided immediate user feedback\n- Local storage approach simplified MVP deployment\nDiscoveries:\n\n- Chakra color system created intuitive category navigation\n- QR code sharing eliminated need for user authentication in MVP\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- Should future versions implement backend authentication or remain browser-local?\n- Which visualization approach (accordion vs mind map) provides better user experience?\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- Deploy application using publish button\n- Test application functionality online\n- Consider adding interactive mind map visualization\n- Evaluate user feedback for future iterations\n---\nUID: 09hdTvRb4eCDX8LIaC6QAz | Model: claude-sonnet-4-20250514 | Cost: $0.0209\n"
